My meme

This meme was obtained from a professor The Simpsons Professor John I.Q. Nerdelbaum Frink Jr.has been a reoccurring character for several seasons. The first time we heard Hank Azarias voice in the role was in the episode Old Money, which aired in 1991. Frink is a brilliant scientist and professor in Springfield, but hes also a bit crazy and socially inept. In times of crisis, Frink often tries to help the town with his bizarre inventions, but he usually makes things worse. His trademark is a style of speaking that includes the impulsive shouting of incoherent nonsense. The motivation behind choosing it is the ability to manipulate the image easily and show the power of magick package in meme processing.

My codes

library(magick)
## Linking to ImageMagick 6.9.12.3
## Enabled features: cairo, freetype, fftw, ghostscript, heic, lcms, pango, raw, rsvg, webp
## Disabled features: fontconfig, x11
frink <- image_read("https://jeroen.github.io/images/frink.png")
print(frink)
##   format width height colorspace matte filesize density
## 1    PNG   220    445       sRGB  TRUE    73494   72x72

##Image border
image_border(image_background(frink, "purple"), "#000080", "20x10")

##Trimming margins
image_trim(frink)

##Image cropping to create a passport size photo\
image_crop(frink, "100x140+50")

##Text annotation
image_annotate(frink, "I like R!", size = 50, gravity = "southwest", color = "pink")

## Annonating
image_annotate(frink, "EXCELLENT", size = 25, color = "purple", boxcolor = "green",
               degrees = 75, location = "+50+100")

## Using the pipe operator
image_read("https://jeroen.github.io/images/frink.png") %>%
  image_rotate(300) %>%
  image_background("red", flatten = TRUE) %>%
  image_border("green", "10x10") %>%
  image_annotate("making use of pipe operator ( %>% ) ", color = "white", size = 25)

##Saving the image as png


image_write(frink, path = "frink.png", format = "png")

My animated GIF

In this part, I created an animated GIF for the old logo of R-programming and the new logo of R-programming I saw it as a fun since I am working with R already to try and create something that incorporates the software itself.

library(magick)

# Combine images
logo <- image_read("https://jeroen.github.io/images/Rlogo.png")
oldlogo <- image_read("https://jeroen.github.io/images/Rlogo-old.png")

# Create morphing animation
both <- image_scale(c(oldlogo, logo), "400")
image_average(image_crop(both))

animation<-image_animate(image_morph(both, 10))

##Saving the animated GIF

animation %>% image_write("my_animation.gif")
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
